text=(:toc-float:)%0a%25rframe%25%25center%25%25fgcolor=red%25%25bgcolor=#ffeeee%25[++This is a draft document, and not a final standard.++]%0a!!!!Definition%0a*Usually set up as for-profit organizations%0a*Can be owned by employees, customers or anyone in a defined set of people%0a*One person, one share, one vote on decisions%0a!!!!Advantages%0a*A Different Purpose: Co-ops and credit unions meet the common needs of their members, whereas most investor-owned businesses exist to maximize profit for shareholders.%0a*A Different Control Structure: Co-ops and credit unions use a system of one-member/one-vote, not one-vote-per-share. This helps them to serve common interests and to ensure that people, not capital, control the organization.%0a*A Different Allocation of Profit: Co-ops and credit unions share profits among their member-owners on the basis of how much they use the organization, not on how many shares they hold.%0a* [-(quoting from http://coopzone.coop/en/coop_advantage)-]%0a!!!!Disadvantages%0a*Slow Decision-Making Speed - everyone must be involved in decisions.%0a*Ineffective Leadership - unless a strong leader appears, leadership and management can be uneven and sometimes ineffective.%0a*Limited Strategic Position - financing can be harder compared to more traditional arrangements.%0a*Talent Deficit - strong entrepreneurial talent is not often attracted to cooperatives because of the limited return for effort.%0a*[-(quoting from http://yourbusiness.azcentral.com/disadvantages-cooperatives-vs-traditional-firms-12745.html)-]%0a!!!!Other Notes%0a*May be philosophically appropriate for organizations committed to sharing resources.%0a*Gives every member a strong sense of ownership.%0a*Can pool a large number of individual resources.%0a*Can be managed in a traditional manner, with a board of directors employing an executive director. The board reports to the entire membership.%0a*Local examples: %25newwin%25[[http://lexington.coop|Lexington Food Cooperative]], %25newwin%25[[http://urbanroots.org|Urban Roots Cooperative Garden Center]]
